# PHP Interview Questions & Answers - Core Rules

This project is a curated collection of PHP interview questions and answers, synchronized between a main `QUESTIONS.md` file, detailed topical files in `answers/`, and a Docusaurus documentation site in `docs/docs/`.

## Key Files & Directories

- **Main Source:** `QUESTIONS.md` (primary source for questions and concise answers)
- **Topical Answers:** `answers/` folder (deep-dive markdown files for complex topics)
- **Documentation:** `docs/docs/` (Docusaurus-formatted content)

## Bi-directional Synchronization

Changes must be synchronized between the root files and the Docusaurus content:
- `QUESTIONS.md` ↔ `docs/docs/questions/`
- `answers/*.md` ↔ `docs/docs/answers/*.md`

Ensure consistency in content, hierarchy, and level categorization across all synchronized files.

## Link Integrity

When reordering sections or renaming files:
- **ALWAYS** perform a global search for links pointing to the affected files.
- **ALWAYS** update relative links in both English and Russian documentation (`docs/docs/` and `docs/i18n/ru/`).
- Verify that internal anchor links (e.g., `[Title](#anchor)`) match the new section numbering.

## Multilingual Synchronization

- **ALWAYS** update the Russian and English versions simultaneously.
- Any change made to English content (`QUESTIONS.md`, `answers/*.md`, `docs/docs/`) **MUST** be immediately reflected in the corresponding Russian files (`translate/ru/`, `docs/i18n/ru/`).
- The structure, numbering, and file naming **MUST** remain identical across both languages.

## README.md Updates

Always update `README.md` if a new topic is covered or a new section is added to ensure the overview remains accurate.
